00:37:41.720 --> 00:37:44.750
and consider how you might apply
some of these best practices

00:37:44.750 --> 00:37:46.380
to your product.

00:37:46.380 --> 00:37:48.230
So a quick run-through--

00:37:48.230 --> 00:37:50.300
we recommend that you
always think about the user

00:37:50.300 --> 00:37:52.790
first, focus on the
user, and all else

00:37:52.790 --> 00:37:56.810
will follow is a mantra we
love to think about here.

00:37:56.810 --> 00:37:57.980
Be clear.

00:37:57.980 --> 00:38:00.410
Write in language
that's free of jargon

00:38:00.410 --> 00:38:03.530
and with sufficient context.

00:38:03.530 --> 00:38:05.090
Be concise.

00:38:05.090 --> 00:38:07.970
Write in a style that's
economical and scannable.

00:38:07.970 --> 00:38:12.110
Remember the F shape pattern
that Allison described.

00:38:12.110 --> 00:38:13.060
Be useful.

00:38:13.060 --> 00:38:15.525
Write in a way that
guides the action.

00:38:15.525 --> 00:38:17.150
And if you don't have
a call to action,

00:38:17.150 --> 00:38:19.660
you might want to add one.

00:38:19.660 --> 00:38:21.120
And be on brand.

00:38:21.120 --> 00:38:25.670
Define your brand voice, and
flex your tone accordingly,

00:38:25.670 --> 00:38:28.400
as Juliana described.

00:38:28.400 --> 00:38:31.280
Finally, whenever
possible, be data-driven.

00:38:31.280 --> 00:38:35.170
If you can apply A/B testing
or other user testing,

00:38:35.170 --> 00:38:38.090
it's a great way to test your
knowledge of your language

00:38:38.090 --> 00:38:41.900
and how well it's
resonating with the user.

